ADO-EKITI- The National Association of Nigerian Students (NANS), has  raised an alarm over an alleged claim destined moves by Omoyele Sowore to conscript the students body into his ill-fated Revolution Now. The students body said it had resolved to resist all ongoing attempts either by Sowore himself or proxies to get the new NANS leadership at all levels to join his Revolution now movement  no matter what The students’  body in a   statement, issued by its  Public Relations Officer, Southwest (Zone D), Olatunji Nurudeen and made available to newsmen in Ado Ekiti alleged that Sowore was deploying his online media platform to cause division  in the association and malign its President. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! NANS said it was disturbing that immediately after the just concluded National convention of NANS in Abuja, without thorough investigation,  Sowore’s medium allegedly went ahead to congratulate another candidate even before official announcement of the actual winner of the poll. “Hence, his decision to continuously promote impersonators of the Zonal officers especially in the South/West through some individuals.” Any Imposition In Choice Of LASU VC, Will Be Rejected- Olarenwaju ASUU Strike Helping B/Haram Achieve Goals NANS said it was unprofessional for Sowore, who it said had no stake in students body  or contested the presidential election with Asefon to allegedly align with students not pleased with his emergence to wanting to bring him down. “It is very unfortunate and uncalled for seeing Mr. Omoyele Sowore and his media workers publishing news from illegal sources just to create division in the association.” “It is also very saddening for Sowore and his partners in Shahara reporters to be working assiduously to destabilize NANS having lured members of our association to join his ‘Revolution now campaign’ with total rejection from Nigerian Students who know he is being sponsored by some individuals who do not want Nigeria to be peaceful. “We can assure Sowore that his plan to split NANS by receiving and publicizing ‘fake news’ from illegitimate sources to create dissention amongst students, most especially South West students is dead on its arrival”, the statement said. “Consequently, NANS want to advise that Sowore should abstain from further encouraging impersonators because we will continue to resist him through every legitimate means at our disposal”, the association said SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION